This definition has been subject to controversy, in particular as lacking operational value, the ambiguity in developing cohesive health strategies, and because of the problem created by use of the word "complete", which makes it practically impossible to achieve.', 'desc': 'Health is the level of functional and metabolic efficiency of a living organism.
